    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - DISASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>DISASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="3">
            <title>GEAR SHIFT LEVER</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Slide the boot up the shift lever shaft and remove (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301764">Figure 64</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301764" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301764" filename="../figg13/G1301764.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 64. Shift Lever Boot</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">With housing bottom facing up, secure the assembly in a vise (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301765">Figure 65</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301765" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301765" filename="../figg13/G1301765.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 65. Forcing Spring</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use large screwdriver to twist between the spring and housing, forcing the spring from
                    under the housing lugs (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301765">Figure 65</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the tension spring, washer, and gear shift lever from the housing tower.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">In models so equipped, remove the nut and washer from the housing bore.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove and inspect the spade pin from the housing; replace if necessary (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301766">Figure 66</hotlnk>).
                </para>
                <figure id="f1301766" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="g1301766" filename="../figg13/G1301766.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 66. Inspect Spade Pin &#38; O-ring</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Inspect the O-ring in the housing groove; replace if necessary (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1301766">Figure 66</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
